<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-02-0195 </DOCNO><TEXT>Energy produced in nuclear plants can make significant contributions tothe non-polluting and low-cost supply of district heating networks. Ifno major nuclear power plant is available in the immediate vicinity ofthe district heating network to be served from which heat could be obtainedthrough cogeneration, heat can be provided by a light water reactor speciallydesigned for this purpose. This kind of supply will be safe, cost effective,and reliable. In line with the requirements of the market, KraftwerkUnion AG (KWU) has included in the development of this line unit sizesof 100 to 500 MWth.</TEXT></DOC>